    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - MXT - RADIATOR and Component INSTALLation - RADIATOR HOSE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>RADIATOR HOSE</title>
        <para>Check radiator hoses prior to installation. Instructions are for both upper and lower radiator tube and
            hose assemblies.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place worm-style hose clamps over each end of new hose (see Figures 17 and 18) (if hose is
                replaced on tube).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position hose over tube end and secure clamp to specifications to form a tight seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check connections to be sure a good seal was made by trying to turn the hose. Hose and clamp
                should not turn when using reasonable torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
